dataIdInfo.envirDesc: Microsoft Windows 7 Version 6.1 (Build 7601) Service Pack 1; Esri ArcGIS 10.3.1.4959
dataIdInfo.idPurp: Points for all Marbled Murrelet surveys performed on ODF managed land.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: Each record is a summary of the survey results from a particular survey visit.

attr.attrdef: Internal feature number.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Contractor, Agency or Cooperator conducting the survey. This has some inaccuracies, as it was post-processed by year. Specifically, some early ODF surveys are identified as ODFW surveys.

edom.edomvd: Oregon Department of Fish and Wildlife
Kim Nelson (Ore. Coop. Fish and Wildlife Unit)

attr.attrdef: ODF District
Site Code assigned by ODF Districts since 1995
Survey Area Name
Sale Unit (has been mostly discontinued, since SITE is more relevant)
Survey Site Number (may change between years of survey)
Survey Station Number (may change between years of survey)
Survey date as DD-MM-YY
Survey year as YYYY
Number of Fly Over Canopy Detections (>1.0 canopy)
Number of Circle Over Canopy Detections (>1.0 canopy)
Number of Circle Below Canopy Detections ( <1.0 canopy)
Number of Fly Through Canopy Detections ( <1.0 canopy)
Number of Landing Detections (rare, usually at nest sites)
Number of Stationary Calling Detections (rare)
Number of Unknown Behavior Detections (usually audio)
Total Number of Detections
The Highest Survey Status observed during the survey
Comments related to detections, weather, etc
Oregon Lambert X coordinate
Oregon Lambert Y coordinate
Concatenation of Site Code, Survey Site Number, and Survey Station Number
Concatenation of Site Code and Survey Site Number
Feature geometry.
